{
  "texts": [
    "Therefore, this approach is a way to extract the part of the input sequence relevant to the task, at the risk of losing some information.",
    "Any NLP model of choice can be applied to further process the extracted texts.",
    "Figure 13 illustrates the approach.",
    "Extractive question answering can be applied without task-specific pre-training, in a fully unsupervised fashion, thus transferring the language-understanding skills from a model that was pre-trained on a large corpus of text data.",
    "Here, we use the deutsche-telekom/bertmulti-english-german-squad2 model provided by HuggingFace."
  ]
}